Correct me if I'm wrong, but AE tash (winds of Tashanian?) is a 4-target spell, and those are the ones where it'll smack the caster if in range, right?  So as far as casting it in general in AE groups, I'd think that the balance between hitting things with your pbae stun, and your 4-target ae tash w/o hitting yourself would be too much trouble.<br>
